<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>This is very similar to bug ZF-464, which pertained to a similar handling in the ORDER BY clause.</p>

<p>Please do not attempt to split comma-separated strings into an array.  Commas may occur in SQL expressions, and it would require a complex parser to distinguish commas that separate terms from commas that appear in SQL expressions.</p>

<p>Instead, just typecast the argument to {{group()}}, {{_tableCols()}}, and {{order()}} to an array.  A simple string will be cast into a one-element array.</p>

<p>If elements must be separate, the user's recommended solution is to use an array.  For example:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$select-&gt;group( array('column1', 'column2') );
</code></pre>

